WEBVTT

00:01.209 --> 00:02.335
[♪♪♪]

00:02.502 --> 00:05.505
-Hey, do you want the rest of my--
-Okay.

00:06.672 --> 00:09.425
-Actually, I was gonna say eggs.
-Okay.

00:10.135 --> 00:12.428
You know, it's not you versus
your cholesterol pills.

00:12.595 --> 00:14.847
You're supposed
to be working together.

00:18.059 --> 00:19.310
I do love my single life...

00:19.477 --> 00:22.272
...but it would be nice to have someone
who didn't want me to die.

00:22.772 --> 00:25.024
Well, you do,
a whole city full of escorts.

00:25.191 --> 00:26.276
[CHUCKLES]

00:26.442 --> 00:29.570
I'm just saying
if you watch the beginning closely...

00:29.737 --> 00:31.489
-...it gives away the ending.
AUDREY: Oh, my God.

00:31.656 --> 00:33.408
-Is he still talking about Inception?
JENNIFER: No.

00:33.574 --> 00:36.327
Rudolph the Red-Nosed Reindeer.

00:36.494 --> 00:39.789
They play the song at the beginning
and it gives away the ending.

00:39.955 --> 00:41.749
It'd be like if at the
beginning of The Sixth Sense...

00:41.916 --> 00:43.000
...they had a song that went:

00:43.168 --> 00:46.129
[SINGING]
Bruce Willis helps a kid
Who sees ghosts

00:46.296 --> 00:49.507
But he's the only one
Who's really dead

00:51.717 --> 00:53.719
Anyway, I'm just here
to grab some food and go.

00:53.886 --> 00:55.012
I'm taking a bus to New Jersey.

00:55.180 --> 00:57.098
-To take the family Christmas picture.
ADAM: Hmm.

00:57.265 --> 01:01.352
-Oh, is Adam going?
-No, my mom wants family only.

01:02.062 --> 01:05.440
And I found the perfect sweater
but whatever....

01:06.107 --> 01:07.108
RUSSELL:
Oh, wait.

01:07.275 --> 01:08.776
You're gonna
miss the office Christmas party.

01:08.943 --> 01:11.404
Oh, guess I'll have to wait
to find out if it was a candy cane...

01:11.571 --> 01:13.198
...in your pocket
or you were just happy to see her.

01:13.364 --> 01:14.365
[RUSSELL CHUCKLES]

01:14.532 --> 01:16.909
Spoiler alert, it was both.

01:18.035 --> 01:19.787
-All right, I'll see you.
-Bye.

01:19.954 --> 01:22.123
Oh, I can't wait
to exchange Christmas presents.

01:22.290 --> 01:23.791
I have the best gift for her.

01:23.958 --> 01:26.001
I made her this coupon book
full of little favors...

01:26.169 --> 01:30.215
...you know, like, um, with hugs
and massages and cuddles.

01:30.381 --> 01:32.675
Cuddles. You gotta be kidding me.

01:33.468 --> 01:36.304
Here's a peek into our home life.

01:36.471 --> 01:39.224
Oh, I have the greatest present
for Jen too.

01:39.390 --> 01:41.642
Uh, no, that's a candy cane.

01:42.101 --> 01:43.978
Excuse me.
Could I get some honey for my tea?

01:44.812 --> 01:46.522
-Throat's a little sore.
-Yeah.

01:46.689 --> 01:48.983
Audrey and I went to a Christmas party
last night and as usual...

01:49.150 --> 01:50.443
...she did the lion's share
of the talking.

01:50.610 --> 01:51.611
RUSSELL:
Heh.

01:51.777 --> 01:55.990
That's because all you ever say is, "Nice
to see you" and "where's the bar?"

01:56.157 --> 01:58.743
I really only care
about the second thing.

01:59.369 --> 02:02.247
Anyway, that's why at parties,
I have to carry us as a couple.

02:02.413 --> 02:04.582
Good thing I'm the funny one.

02:09.086 --> 02:11.046
-You're the funny one?
-You knew that.

02:11.214 --> 02:13.383
I don't think anyone knew that.

02:13.549 --> 02:16.010
-Audrey, I think you're funny.
-Thank you.

02:16.177 --> 02:18.304
Remember that time
she wore that gray coat...

02:18.471 --> 02:21.307
...and it was like so ridiculous
with the straps all over it everywhere.

02:21.474 --> 02:23.351
Oh, yeah, yeah,
that was hilarious.

02:23.518 --> 02:25.936
And Jeff said she looked
like a Civil War general.

02:26.103 --> 02:27.522
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

02:28.731 --> 02:32.527
-Jackets like that are in.
-In 1863.

02:32.693 --> 02:34.695
"My dearest Annabel...

02:34.862 --> 02:38.449
...the war rages on
but I must thank you for the...

02:38.616 --> 02:41.035
-...fine garments you...
ADAM: Heh.

02:41.494 --> 02:42.620
...procure."

02:42.787 --> 02:43.913
[LAUGHS]

02:44.747 --> 02:47.625
Actually, Audrey
is the butt of those jokes...

02:47.792 --> 02:49.710
-...you would be the butt of the couple.
-Ahem.

02:49.877 --> 02:50.961
Mm-hm.

02:51.128 --> 02:53.839
See, I don't have to resort
to cheap shots and insults.

02:54.006 --> 02:55.508
Like last night,
I got a great reaction...

02:55.675 --> 02:58.052
...when I told that story
about our trip to Oahu.

02:58.678 --> 03:01.681
I think it's pronounced Ohio.

03:04.016 --> 03:06.352
Um, it's in Hawaii.

03:06.519 --> 03:12.483
Heh, jeez. Somebody get her a map.

03:15.820 --> 03:17.154
[SEÑOR HAPPY'S
"HOW MAY WAYS" PLAYING]

03:17.322 --> 03:19.532
♪ How may ways
To say I love you ♪

03:21.784 --> 03:25.496
♪ How many ways
To say that I'm not scared ♪

03:26.163 --> 03:30.876
♪ With you by my side
There is no denying ♪

03:31.043 --> 03:34.464
♪ I can't wait for me and you ♪♪

03:39.051 --> 03:40.636
[♪♪♪]

03:42.555 --> 03:45.933
Timmy, it's gonna
be a very Merry Christmas.

03:46.434 --> 03:49.729
Or whatever creepy
pagan ritual you observe.

03:50.271 --> 03:53.774
What accounts for your anticipation
of said merriment, sir?

03:53.941 --> 03:58.488
I accidentally stumbled upon Adam's
homemade Christmas coupons for Jen.

03:58.654 --> 04:00.448
You mean went into
his office and stole.

04:01.741 --> 04:03.993
Stumbled upon, yes.

04:04.452 --> 04:06.371
Oh, dear me. He's certainly
liberal with the glitter, isn't he?

04:06.537 --> 04:07.538
[RUSSELL CHUCKLES]

04:07.705 --> 04:12.084
Yes, he is. But I figure, why restrict
Adam's generosity to Jen...

04:12.252 --> 04:14.211
...when the joy could
be spread to so many?

04:15.045 --> 04:19.091
I mean, who wouldn't want a backrub
from Adam?

04:20.968 --> 04:25.014
Or who wouldn't want, heh,
a shampooing from Adam?

04:25.180 --> 04:27.475
Hey, who's that
white kid in shipping...

04:27.642 --> 04:29.977
...with the nasty dreads
with the bugs in them?

04:30.853 --> 04:34.023
-That would be Nate.
-Nate. Ah, good old Nate.

04:35.983 --> 04:37.026
What's wrong?

04:37.192 --> 04:38.778
I'm having fun at someone's expense
and it's not yours.

04:38.944 --> 04:40.780
You should be enjoying this.

04:41.364 --> 04:44.367
I suppose I'm still wistful
about my breakup with Allison, sir.

04:44.534 --> 04:47.202
I guess long-distance relationships
are just too difficult--

04:47.370 --> 04:49.289
To listen to. Yeah.

04:50.540 --> 04:51.541
You know what?

04:51.707 --> 04:54.419
I think the office Christmas party
is the perfect thing to cheer you up.

04:55.586 --> 04:57.588
I'm not sure,
I'm in the mood for a party.

04:58.423 --> 05:02.385
Oh, come on, let's put Allison behind
you and some other bimbo under you.

05:03.093 --> 05:04.554
Perhaps it is time for me to move on.

05:04.720 --> 05:07.307
I guess I won't meet anybody new
just sitting at home.

05:07.473 --> 05:08.474
I wanna help you out.

05:08.641 --> 05:11.352
How about I make you
official party greeter?

05:12.269 --> 05:13.479
Oh, I'd be honored, sir.

05:13.646 --> 05:16.023
Yeah. And I'm sorry
about you and Allison.

05:16.190 --> 05:17.191
Would a hug help?

05:17.858 --> 05:19.819
-You know, it just might.
-Oh, here you go, buddy.

05:21.696 --> 05:22.988
[♪♪♪]

05:26.367 --> 05:29.829
Wow, your company really stepped
it up this year.

05:29.995 --> 05:32.289
I'll reserve judgment
until I see the size of the shrimp.

05:32.457 --> 05:33.541
[AUDREY CHUCKLES]

05:33.708 --> 05:35.250
-Hey, Jeff.
-Oh, hey, nice to see you.

05:35.418 --> 05:36.461
Where's the bar?

05:36.627 --> 05:37.628
[DAN CHUCKLES]

05:37.795 --> 05:38.796
It's right over there.

05:38.963 --> 05:40.506
Audrey, you remember
Dan and his girlfriend Barbara?

05:40.673 --> 05:42.550
-Hi.
-Actually, it's fiancée.

05:42.717 --> 05:45.302
Oh, Dan and his girlfriend fiancée.
That's lovely.

05:45.845 --> 05:48.848
No, her name is Barbara.
We just got engaged.

05:49.014 --> 05:51.684
-Oh, well, that makes sense.
-Congratulations.

05:51.851 --> 05:53.102
-Thank you.
JEFF: Hey, little advice.

05:53.268 --> 05:56.647
On the road to marriage,
don't be afraid to drive drunk.

05:56.814 --> 05:58.483
[ALL LAUGH]

05:58.649 --> 06:00.860
And if you are gonna
follow his roadmap...

06:01.026 --> 06:03.904
...don't get lost because
he's not gonna ask for directions.

06:04.071 --> 06:05.155
[CHUCKLES]

06:07.908 --> 06:10.870
Why would I ask for directions
if, uh, we have a roadmap?

06:11.036 --> 06:13.247
Uh, no, that's why it's funny, heh.

06:13.414 --> 06:15.750
You know, because guys
don't ask for directions.

06:15.916 --> 06:17.418
Dan does.

06:18.168 --> 06:20.921
Okay. But that's unusual, tsk.

06:21.088 --> 06:22.923
Especially now
that everybody's got GPS.

06:23.090 --> 06:24.091
[BOTH LAUGH]

06:24.258 --> 06:25.635
GPS, heh.

06:25.801 --> 06:29.639
That wasn't even a joke.
He was just stating the facts.

06:29.805 --> 06:30.848
Must be the way he said it.

06:31.015 --> 06:33.183
[BOTH LAUGH]

06:33.350 --> 06:35.728
-Uh, what are you doing?
-What do you mean?

06:35.895 --> 06:38.939
Wait, are you trying to prove
that you're the funny one?

06:39.482 --> 06:40.525
No.

06:40.691 --> 06:43.402
Because if you are, I'll run home
and grab that Civil War jacket for you.

06:44.403 --> 06:45.946
They're very in.

06:48.658 --> 06:49.784
[♪♪♪]

06:52.453 --> 06:54.747
Come out, Timmy.

06:54.914 --> 06:56.415
TIMMY:
Mr. Dunbar?

06:56.582 --> 07:00.961
When I agreed to be the party greeter,
I did not agree to this.

07:01.128 --> 07:04.256
Come on, chicks dig
a man in uniform.

07:05.841 --> 07:06.842
Yeah, heh.

07:07.009 --> 07:08.844
Ha-ha-ha. Oh, whoa.

07:10.930 --> 07:14.809
Okay, don we now our gay apparel.
I finally get that.

07:14.975 --> 07:17.478
That's your way of encouraging
me to stay in this outfit?

07:17.645 --> 07:19.564
No, my way of encouraging you
to stay in the outfit...

07:19.730 --> 07:21.941
...was throwing your clothes down
the garbage chute.

07:22.399 --> 07:23.734
-Come on, let's hit the par-tay.
-No, sir.

07:23.901 --> 07:25.069
[RUSSELL WHISTLES]

07:25.235 --> 07:27.447
I'm leaving here
with what's left of my dignity.

07:27.613 --> 07:28.656
[BELLS JINGLING]

07:28.823 --> 07:32.201
Heh, heh. Oh, no, he's got little bells
on his shoes.

07:32.367 --> 07:33.744
It's too good, heh.

07:35.746 --> 07:37.039
[BELLS JINGLING]

07:38.040 --> 07:40.292
-I see what you're trying to do.
-Hmm.

07:40.460 --> 07:42.587
You're trying to humiliate me
for your own amusement.

07:42.753 --> 07:45.923
But you know what? I am not going
to give you the satisfaction.

07:46.090 --> 07:49.760
-I'm staying.
-Oh, that'll show me.

07:49.927 --> 07:53.514
I'll show you,
by wearing this ensemble with pride.

07:53.681 --> 07:57.184
I don't know if using the word
"ensemble" is helping your cause.

07:57.351 --> 08:01.355
-Go ahead, sir. Mock away.
-Well, I'm trying. Stop interrupting.

08:01.897 --> 08:03.733
You're going to be the one
who's disappointed when people...

08:03.899 --> 08:06.235
...rally around my costume
and appreciate its holiday spirit--

08:06.401 --> 08:07.528
-Okay.
-Ladies, welcome.

08:07.695 --> 08:08.946
As your official greeter...

08:09.113 --> 08:10.615
...please allow me
to point out that the bar...

08:10.781 --> 08:12.407
...and light hors d'oeuvres
are that way.

08:12.575 --> 08:14.744
Thanks. Hey, which way
to the guys with pants?

08:14.910 --> 08:17.329
[RUSSELL CHUCKLES]

08:19.081 --> 08:21.542
Aw, and they didn't even
hear you walk.

08:22.459 --> 08:24.461
[BELLS JINGLING]

08:24.629 --> 08:26.130
[♪♪♪]

08:28.508 --> 08:30.175
Oh, Adam.

08:30.342 --> 08:32.512
Thanks so much for the gift.

08:34.263 --> 08:36.516
Gift. Uh, what gift is that?

08:36.682 --> 08:40.102
One of your special
super-squeeze, hugs.

08:43.480 --> 08:46.859
-Wait a minute. Where'd you get that?
-It was in my Christmas stocking.

08:51.155 --> 08:52.823
Okay, um....

08:52.990 --> 08:56.243
Look, Evelyn, there's been
a bit of a misunderstanding, um....

08:56.410 --> 08:58.412
That coupon wasn't meant for you.

08:59.997 --> 09:02.291
Oh, that's too bad.

09:02.457 --> 09:05.711
I've had kind of a rough week
with the subway incident and all.

09:06.587 --> 09:09.674
I could have really used a hug.

09:12.134 --> 09:13.678
ADAM:
Wait.

09:15.638 --> 09:19.224
I am a man of my word.
Get over here, you.

09:21.894 --> 09:23.771
EVELYN:
Mm.

09:30.027 --> 09:34.740
-Feel better?
-The coupon says two full minutes.

09:36.325 --> 09:38.202
That's why you work in legal.

09:42.497 --> 09:44.709
Oh, hey, there you are.

09:44.875 --> 09:48.170
Wish I could've found you sooner
but you know guys...

09:48.337 --> 09:51.131
...we don't ask for directions, heh.

09:51.298 --> 09:56.053
Shut up.
Stupid Dan and his dumb fiancée.

09:56.220 --> 09:58.681
-How could they not know about that?
-I don't know.

09:58.848 --> 10:02.142
Maybe they're not hip to the stand-up
comedy themes of the '80s.

10:02.643 --> 10:04.103
You know what I should do.

10:04.269 --> 10:07.898
-Try to relax and have fun?
-Oh, you'd like that, wouldn't you?

10:08.774 --> 10:09.942
Yeah.

10:10.651 --> 10:14.488
No, I'm gonna bust out my Hawaii story
and you are gonna set me up.

10:14.655 --> 10:18.575
So start talking
about islands or vacations.

10:18.743 --> 10:20.202
Oh, there's pineapple on the buffet.

10:20.369 --> 10:22.162
I don't need you.

10:22.747 --> 10:24.665
Why has it become such a big deal
all of a sudden...

10:24.832 --> 10:25.833
...for you to be the funny one?

10:26.000 --> 10:27.209
Who said it's a big deal?

10:27.376 --> 10:29.544
Oh, come on. I saw you making
notes on a napkin over there.

10:29.712 --> 10:33.090
Maybe because I'm not working.
I'm self-conscious about that.

10:33.257 --> 10:35.050
Audrey, you don't have to be
self-conscious about anything.

10:35.217 --> 10:38.387
You're charming. You're beautiful.

10:39.054 --> 10:41.306
Oh, that's sweet.

10:41.473 --> 10:43.768
And I know you mean it
because that's the first drink.

10:43.934 --> 10:45.060
[AUDREY CHUCKLES]

10:46.270 --> 10:47.437
Second?

10:49.982 --> 10:52.067
We've been here like eight minutes.

10:53.152 --> 10:54.319
Time for a refill.

10:56.405 --> 10:57.406
[SIGHS]

10:57.572 --> 11:01.201
And my grandmother had a heart attack
right on Waikiki beach...

11:01.368 --> 11:04.163
...so we had to drop everything
and fly there.

11:04.329 --> 11:07.249
Straight from the airport
to the morgue.

11:07.416 --> 11:10.210
Not exactly a dream trip to Hawaii.

11:10.377 --> 11:12.337
Excuse me.

11:12.838 --> 11:16.675
I couldn't help but overhearing.
Did someone just say Hawaii?

11:20.012 --> 11:21.430
[♪♪♪]

11:23.933 --> 11:25.017
You know...

11:25.184 --> 11:28.938
...the last time I saw legs like that they
were curled up under Dorothy's house.

11:31.356 --> 11:32.399
Good one, sir.

11:32.566 --> 11:35.569
Now, if you'll please excuse me,
I have more good cheer to spread.

11:35.736 --> 11:38.906
By letting everyone make fun of you?
Here, I'll help. Check this out.

11:39.698 --> 11:43.160
These days even the North Pole
is outsourcing.

11:43.577 --> 11:46.038
He's Indian. Keep walking.

11:47.164 --> 11:48.540
Ha-ha-ha.

11:48.707 --> 11:49.708
[BELLS JINGLING]

11:49.875 --> 11:52.002
Are we hearing these bells, people?

11:52.753 --> 11:56.006
So originally, the coupons
were for my fiancée...

11:56.173 --> 12:00.594
...then Russell,
who shall remain nameless...

12:01.220 --> 12:06.058
...gave them out.
You know what? I'm rolling with it.

12:06.225 --> 12:07.684
How's the pressure, Vic?

12:10.312 --> 12:12.689
You can go a little deeper.

12:13.357 --> 12:14.399
[♪♪♪]

12:14.817 --> 12:18.779
So day five, still no luggage.
Finally, we go to check out.

12:18.946 --> 12:21.073
What do we see at the bell desk?
Our bags.

12:21.240 --> 12:24.952
Which had been there
the entire time, ha, ha.

12:25.119 --> 12:28.455
I mean, can you imagine
a worse trip to Hawaii?

12:28.622 --> 12:30.207
[LAUGHS]

12:40.885 --> 12:42.386
Hawaii story?

12:44.972 --> 12:47.391
Wish I could say I was surprised.

13:02.697 --> 13:04.158
Okay. There you go, Pearl.

13:04.324 --> 13:05.868
You should get
that bunion checked out.

13:06.035 --> 13:07.744
It's a little angry.

13:10.831 --> 13:13.000
Uh, aren't you forgetting something?

13:15.169 --> 13:17.171
Merry Christmas.

13:18.172 --> 13:20.549
I can't believe
you're actually doing this stuff.

13:20.715 --> 13:23.218
Well, it was a little awkward at first,
but I'm brightening their day...

13:23.385 --> 13:25.762
...which makes my Christmas
even better.

13:25.930 --> 13:28.473
Better? It's supposed to be worse.

13:28.974 --> 13:31.768
Well, I'm sorry,
but your little prank backfired.

13:31.936 --> 13:36.440
Plus, I can still give the coupons to Jen
now that I got them all back, heh, heh.

13:36.606 --> 13:39.026
-Ah, nertz.
-Yep.

13:42.029 --> 13:44.614
Wait a minute. They're not all here.

13:44.781 --> 13:46.951
-Hey, Adam.
-Oh, hey, Scotty.

13:47.117 --> 13:49.744
-I'd like to cash this in.
-Oh.

13:51.455 --> 13:53.123
Oh.

13:54.666 --> 13:59.129
Hey, hey,
how about a little foot rub...

13:59.296 --> 14:01.590
...or maybe
a nice back massage instead?

14:02.925 --> 14:04.509
I want that one.

14:07.804 --> 14:10.265
Okay, Scotty. Let's do this.

14:14.686 --> 14:15.896
[♪♪♪]

14:18.148 --> 14:20.317
-You okay?
-Uh, well...

14:20.484 --> 14:23.612
...I told what I thought was a funny story
and it made a woman cry.

14:23.778 --> 14:27.116
Was it the "asking for directions" thing
because I don't really get it.

14:27.282 --> 14:29.201
But it didn't make me cry.

14:29.368 --> 14:33.830
Ugh, maybe Jeff's right.
He thinks I try too hard at parties.

14:33.998 --> 14:36.375
Look how hard
he's working the buffet.

14:36.541 --> 14:37.960
[BARBARA CHUCKLES]

14:38.127 --> 14:39.669
Oh, God.

14:39.836 --> 14:42.422
Look at the poor guy
stuck behind him.

14:42.589 --> 14:45.092
Get that guy a magazine.
It's gonna be a while, pal.

14:45.259 --> 14:46.593
[BARBARA CHUCKLES]

14:47.386 --> 14:50.139
He looks like a whale
scooping up plankton.

14:50.305 --> 14:51.306
[LAUGHING]

14:51.473 --> 14:52.807
That's hilarious.

14:52.975 --> 14:53.976
-It is?
BARBARA: Heh.

14:54.143 --> 14:55.144
What's so funny?

14:55.310 --> 14:59.314
-Audrey's talking about Jeff.
-He looks like a bear with a tapeworm.

14:59.481 --> 15:00.732
[BOTH LAUGHING]

15:00.900 --> 15:01.901
Tapeworm.

15:02.067 --> 15:03.485
[LAUGHING]

15:03.652 --> 15:06.113
AUDREY: Now, check it out.
Now he's stuck behind someone.

15:06.280 --> 15:11.035
Watch him pull the old tap and slide.
Tap and slide.

15:11.201 --> 15:13.996
[BARBARA AND DAN LAUGHING]

15:14.204 --> 15:15.497
[♪♪♪]

15:15.705 --> 15:16.916
[ALL LAUGHING]

15:17.082 --> 15:21.253
So after dinner, there's Jeff passed out
at the table, hands down his pants.

15:21.420 --> 15:22.754
[LAUGHING]

15:22.922 --> 15:24.798
All in all, not a great first Thanksgiving
with my parents.

15:26.341 --> 15:29.886
Oh, here he comes. I bet he asks
the location of a food item.

15:31.221 --> 15:33.557
Hey, Aud, did you see where
the stuffed-mushroom guy went?

15:33.723 --> 15:35.684
[LAUGHING]

15:41.065 --> 15:42.149
It's a gift.

15:43.400 --> 15:45.360
Anyway, it looked like you
were doing great.

15:45.527 --> 15:48.072
I was. Felt pretty good.

15:48.238 --> 15:50.240
And you know,
couldn't have done it without you.

15:50.407 --> 15:55.787
-So you learned from the master.
-Heh, you were definitely my inspiration.

15:56.913 --> 15:57.957
Let's go.

15:58.123 --> 15:59.208
[AUDREY CLEARS THROAT]

15:59.374 --> 16:00.709
[♪♪♪]

16:00.875 --> 16:03.087
All right. Thank you.

16:03.253 --> 16:06.548
You know, I can't believe
they make you wear this getup.

16:06.715 --> 16:08.800
Nobody made me.
I wore this myself.

16:09.509 --> 16:11.595
Why would you do that?

16:12.304 --> 16:14.639
Because it's Christmas
and if you can't have fun...

16:14.806 --> 16:16.766
...and loosen up on Christmas,
when can you?

16:16.933 --> 16:18.227
Ah.

16:18.393 --> 16:19.979
Hey, speaking of loosening up--

16:20.145 --> 16:22.939
I have no interest in hearing
how that sentence ends.

16:24.191 --> 16:29.404
-Come on, can't you let a guy try?
-Sorry, you're not really my type.

16:29.571 --> 16:33.450
-Really? What's your type?
-Someone who embraces the joy...

16:33.617 --> 16:34.618
-...of the holidays.
-Oh.

16:34.784 --> 16:38.580
Someone who gets into the fun
and the spirit of Christmas.

16:39.623 --> 16:41.500
[CHRISTMAS MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

17:03.438 --> 17:05.649
Christmas nertz.

17:18.245 --> 17:22.249
Oh, nothing on the coupon
about that, Scotty.

17:30.215 --> 17:31.300
[♪♪♪]

17:34.178 --> 17:35.429
You know what is not good?

17:36.180 --> 17:38.890
Diner Eggnog

17:40.225 --> 17:41.935
-Really? Let me try it.
-Get your own.

17:42.102 --> 17:43.270
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

17:43.437 --> 17:45.439
Oh, here it is.

17:45.605 --> 17:48.150
My mom sent me
our family Christmas photo.

17:48.317 --> 17:51.195
Oh, well, wait. I thought
Adam wasn't gonna be in it.

17:51.361 --> 17:52.779
Oh, that's my cousin Cynthia.

17:52.946 --> 17:54.948
Something's going on
with her hormone-wise.

17:56.658 --> 17:57.784
[RUSSELL GROANS]

17:57.951 --> 17:59.328
Oh, what's the matter?

17:59.494 --> 18:02.456
Ghost of Christmas Future
come bearing test results?

18:03.832 --> 18:05.584
Can we skip the pleasantries?

18:06.918 --> 18:08.253
What's your problem?

18:08.420 --> 18:11.256
My problem is I tried to ruin all
my friends' Christmases...

18:11.423 --> 18:13.092
...and they had fun anyway.

18:13.800 --> 18:15.885
What's the matter with you?

18:16.886 --> 18:19.223
You're gonna have to be
more specific.

18:20.265 --> 18:23.268
You're sad because you weren't able
to ruin Christmas for other people.

18:23.435 --> 18:26.020
I am. But maybe you're right.

18:26.188 --> 18:28.022
Maybe that's not what
Christmas is all about.

18:29.065 --> 18:32.402
Maybe, you think
maybe it might not be about that?

18:33.570 --> 18:35.697
Why are you so against
people enjoying Christmas?

18:35.864 --> 18:37.782
Because I never did.

18:37.949 --> 18:41.661
When I was a kid, every December,
my parents went to the Bahamas...

18:41.828 --> 18:43.788
...and left me at home
with my nanny Helga.

18:43.955 --> 18:47.501
Oh, poor Helga.

18:48.627 --> 18:51.921
You're trying to make others feel awful
because misery loves company.

18:52.088 --> 18:56.218
See, Jeff agrees with
and approves of my behavior.

18:57.511 --> 19:01.181
But maybe I should
try to change my holiday spirit.

19:01.348 --> 19:05.101
You should. I wasn't really looking
forward to the holidays this year.

19:05.269 --> 19:08.355
But it looks like it's gonna be
a Merry Christmas after all.

19:08.522 --> 19:09.523
Oh.

19:09.689 --> 19:11.233
RUSSELL:
Oh, my God.

19:11.400 --> 19:13.568
I unscrewed that last night, heh.

19:15.237 --> 19:18.907
It's a Christmas miracle.
God bless us all, every one.

19:19.073 --> 19:20.492
[♪♪♪]

19:22.327 --> 19:23.453
[♪♪♪]

19:23.620 --> 19:27.123
Okay. So I know
it's not Christmas yet...

19:27.291 --> 19:29.293
...but I wanna give you
your present now.

19:30.084 --> 19:32.712
-Oh, it's so cute.
ADAM: Heh.

19:32.879 --> 19:33.880
[GASPS]

19:34.047 --> 19:36.090
-Oh, cuddles.
-Yep.

19:36.258 --> 19:37.592
-Massage.
-Mm-hm.

19:37.759 --> 19:40.220
Breakfast in bed.

19:40.387 --> 19:42.639
Oh, my gosh. And these are
all actually gifts for me.

19:42.806 --> 19:45.058
None of them is really a gift for you.

19:45.225 --> 19:49.604
Well, there is one in there
that's kind of a gift for me.

19:50.939 --> 19:52.274
-I don't see it.
-Huh?

19:52.441 --> 19:53.900
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

19:58.405 --> 20:01.157
Oh, come on, Scotty.

20:05.579 --> 20:07.456
I'll be right back.

20:11.751 --> 20:13.420
What, you have to talk to that guy?

20:14.254 --> 20:15.880
Talk?

20:17.006 --> 20:18.091
I wish.

20:22.387 --> 20:24.223
[♪♪♪]

20:28.393 --> 20:30.604
[♪♪♪]
